243
00:24:54,800 --> 00:25:03,500
And they would never let them freeze or spoil [what they had caught] saying that the fish traps would not get fish anymore.

244
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:14,000
Because there is a lot of that now, and drift nets spoiling [catch],
the fish are depleting.

245
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:20,500
We must understand that God has cursed us through that.

246
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:30,000
We have worsening shortages of things, shortages of fish,
the food that we are given.

247
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:37,000
My goodness, let all of us elders be in accordance

248
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:44,500
Let us instruct our descendants to take care of this land
to keep it pristine.

249
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:52,500
When it is pristine again, God will certainly bless it our of gratitude.

250
00:25:53,500 --> 00:26:05,000
When he blesses it, the things we eat, sell, and gather
will increase all in the same way.

251
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:15,500
I am thankful when I hear people sometimes talking
[about traditional wisdom] on the radio.

252
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:20,000
This important thought that I had last spring

253
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:28,000
I am speaking to all of you who are listening about
what I wanted to say about the things I saw with my own eyes.

254
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:34,900
We must raise up our young people to be like that.

255
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:45,500
Now, I have been like that with my children for a long time,
telling them to clean up regularly.

256
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:53,500
And I have them watch me as I clean up in front of them,
and have them watch me clean up our fish camp.

257
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,500
I also tell them not to throw these empty motor oil cans into the water.

258
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:08,000
I wrap them in plastic and throw them into holes that I dug in the ground.

259
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:17,500
I don’t only tell them, but instruct my children on what I do
by having them watch me.

260
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:22,500
We fathers and mothers must do that

261
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:27,900
To respect our land like our ancestors since the beginning

262
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:32,500
And to watch over, use it well, and keep it pristine.

263
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:38,000
My, we will do well if we do that.

264
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:45,000
Will God not thank us in the last day?

265
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:50,000
Will he not tell us that we cleaned up his land?

266
00:27:51,000 --> 00:28:02,500
Because he owns it, he certainly made those who cleaned up
into great hunters a long time ago.

267
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,900
Begin with that.

268
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:08,900
There is a lot to this.

269
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:14,000
I’ve said what I wanted to say when I arrived.

270
00:28:14,100 --> 00:28:23,000
I also talk about how to clean up both the land and water in churches.

271
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:25,000
Respect them.

272
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:27,500
There is so much to this.

273
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:41,800
Let us all not fail to raise up our young people
and tell them to keep this [earth] pristine.

274
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:44,400
I say this to my children:

275
00:28:44,500 --> 00:28:50,500
Even if you had slept there for the night, always leave it cleaned up.

276
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,000
We must tell them that.

277
00:28:53,700 --> 00:28:57,900
These days, I also see used diapers

278
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:03,000
The used diapers of their loved ones are [scattered], a lot.

279
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:09,000
Are those not a cause for ingratitude in God’s eyes?

280
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:17,700
It’s time for us to take care of our land in accordance like our ancestors,
keep it cleaned up.

281
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:22,000
Thank you. I thank you if you’re listening.

282
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:31,500
I will also try to do that as I’ve said as much as I can.

283
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:37,000
Thank you, I have told you what I think is important.

