00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,400
Sometime recently, one of your daughters

294
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:35,000
When we interviewed one of your daughters, [s]he asked her now she was raised.

295
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:39,000
And then she said that this is what she thought:

296
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:50,000
When one of their peers misbehaved, your late wife
would gather them all and admonish them.

297
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:57,000
How is admonishing like that now

298
00:30:57,500 --> 00:31:02,000
You know, we’ve started hear know that people only discriminate
against someone who misbehaves.

299
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:07,500
And some who are families do not love him too much

300
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:14,000
Separating him because he’s mischievous, disobedient,
an alcoholic, or something else.

301
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:25,000
How did you and your late wife raise your children?

302
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,000
What is raising a child like?

303
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:37,500
Child rearing is also part of the traditional wisdom
from our ancestors back then.

304
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:51,000
My father raised me back then, and probably when I needed it,
he would instruct me without regard [for my feelings].

305
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:59,500
Or, he would also gather my family and my older sisters
to instruct us on how we should live.

306
00:31:59,800 --> 00:32:02,000
And then they would say this to us:

307
00:32:03,400 --> 00:32:11,000
“Do not despise your peers in life. Instead, humble yourselves
before them in life.”

308
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:24,000
Adhering to that ancient piece of wisdom, our pride should be
as much as what they tread upon in our live.

309
00:32:24,100 --> 00:32:29,000
Let us be as humble as the grass they tread upon.

310
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:39,000
And then they asked me when I took a wife and had children

311
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:46,000
When I had children my father said to me, “You are now a father.

312
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:51,500
“You are now an instructor for your child who is born.

313
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:56,700
“I will not teach or instruct you.

314
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:06,000
“I have already instructed you on what you should
pass on to your child whom you love.

315
00:33:06,700 --> 00:33:11,500
“I have also talked to you about what has not originated from me.

316
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:16,000
“I’ve passed on my father’s traditional wisdom onto you.

317
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:24,500
“You are doing that, but I will watch you.
I will admonish you when you warrant it.”

318
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:31,500
And then this: “Children are different.”

319
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:40,000
Now I have nine children.

320
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:48,000
Five are male, and three are female.

321
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:58,400
These people are different. One of them tends to be mischievous
and disregards [instruction or wisdom].

322
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:03,000
They’re evidently different as our ancestors back then have said.

323
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:09,000
They say that descendants are different even when they shared a womb.

324
00:34:09,500 --> 00:34:11,000
That’s what they say.

325
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:19,500
But even though they are different, compassion is the most important
piece of traditional wisdom.

326
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,500
They also used to tell us this:

327
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:30,500
“If one of your family members is mischievous and disobedient

328
00:34:30,600 --> 00:34:37,500
“Because youpl, his siblings, try not to be like that in life

329
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:45,400
“Youpl, his siblings, must gather and admonish him.

330
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:53,500
“Do not scold or criticize him, but treat him well with love.

331
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:59,000
“And do not speak harshly, but with tenderhearted love.

332
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:06,000
“Because yourpl sibling is like that, youpl must admonish him with love.”

333
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:18,000
And then if you take in a son-in-law, it’s an ancient custom

334
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:30,500
If you take in a son-in-law, love him more than your own children.

335
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:42,000
No matter what he does, do not react violently to him, but speak to him
and instruct him with tenderhearted love.

336
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:51,000
My son-in-law is [mischievous] like that,
and he abuses this alcohol

337
00:35:51,500 --> 00:36:00,000
But I have never spoken harshly to him to this day
according to what I was instructed.

338
00:36:00,100 --> 00:36:12,000
Concerning what little instruction I gave [him], I talked about that wisdom
with tenderhearted love for my own son-in-law.

339
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:19,000
That’s why my son-in-law cannot leave me alone today.

340
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:24,000
And if he seens that I need something, he will help me.

341
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:29,500
That’s what trying to treat everyone with love is like.

342
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:33,800
We must be like that.

343
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:40,000
And then, I think I just talked about it first

344
00:36:40,500 --> 00:36:46,500
That I should not join others in criticizing mischievous people.

345
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:53,000
That is traditional wisdom from our ancestors.

346
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:59,200
They say that a [Christian] believer…

347
00:36:59,300 --> 00:37:07,000
Back then, they didn’t talk about believers, but obedient people.

348
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:12,500
Instead, they called believers obedient.

349
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:16,000
These days, they call them [Christian] believers.

350
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:21,900
Back then, however, our ancestors called them qanrucunalriit

351
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:34,500
They referred to someone who did not do whatever he wanted
but adhered to his instructions as obedient.

352
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:43,000
These days, however, we are called believers,
call that obedient person [a believer].

353
00:37:44,700 --> 00:37:57,500
They told us to be like that so that we would stand [alive] for a long time
and that we would be given long-lasting strength.

354
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:03,000
These are evidently instructions saying this,

355
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:08,000
After they instructed us, they would say this:

356
00:38:08,100 --> 00:38:15,000
“A person instruction whom he loves so that [s]he will live well.”

357
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:32,500
Jesus further explained those with his words
saying this to his disciples in John 6 verse 63.

358
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:38,000
John 6 verse 63, Jesus explicitly said,

359
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:47,000
“My words to you are breath and life.”

360
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:54,000
Here is wisdom from back before our ancestors before there was a Bible:

361
00:38:54,800 --> 00:39:06,000
If you, a great hunter, come upon misfortune that you cannot survive

362
00:39:06,500 --> 00:39:14,800
If you flustered and do not remember the traditional wisdom you heard

363
00:39:14,900 --> 00:39:20,500
If you do not remember them, you will die by your own fault.

364
00:39:21,500 --> 00:39:29,500
Yet even if you come upon misfortune, if you remember traditional wisdom

365
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:38,000
The wisdom you remember will give you strength and save you from that.

366
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:45,500
That is apparently how these instructions are breath and life.

367
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:49,500
We must adhere to them.

368
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:54,000
They would also tell us this:

369
00:39:54,900 --> 00:40:00,000
“Quit being so noisy. Do not act so mindlessly.”

370
00:40:00,100 --> 00:40:04,000
They would also tell us that when we made too much noise in our homes.

371
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:11,500
Behold the precious young people these days

372
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:20,000
They even fill a huge plane and bring them to other villages
to make a lot of noise.

373
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:23,000
They say they’re bringing them to play basketball.

374
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:27,500
Yet there was this instruction among our ancestors:

375
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:39,000
If you bring this growing boy do other villages,
he will be mischievous.

376
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:45,500
And even in other villages where he has never been or seen

377
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:51,500
He will be able to be noisy there without shame when he arrives.

378
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:58,900
They say that’s what one who was brought to outside villages
when he was growing up has always been like.

379
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:03,000
Because those ancestors have seen that

380
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:09,900
They tell people not to bring a growing child to others’ houses
in their villages.

381
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:14,000
Or, they tell people not to bring them to other villages.

382
00:41:14,500 --> 00:41:18,000
That is the instruction of our ancestors back then.

383
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:27,500
They say that if we want a mindful child, we will adhere to that.

384
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:36,000
We would not bring our children whom we love to other’s houses,
and we won’t bring them to other [villages].

385
00:41:38,500 --> 00:41:41,500
They say that some would say this:

386
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:47,000
“That person is sensible, wise, and articulate.”

387
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:53,500
They say that’s what people who were not taken to other places
when they were growing are like.

388
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:59,000
Those are true pieces of wisdom from our ancestors.

389
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:07,500
Our ancestors back then teach things, true things, that they have seen.

390
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,000
There you have it.

391
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:29,000
And then they said that even if we are short on something as we live,
