392
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:36,000
They told us not to steal, or to take another person’s catches.

393
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:39,000
They said this:

394
00:42:40,300 --> 00:42:46,000
“If you take that mink or fox

395
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:55,000
“Your caretaker, God, the Spirit of the Universe,
will let what was prepared to be yours be taken.

396
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:01,500
“If you take that, you will take one

397
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:13,000
“But God will exchange what was supposed to be yours to the
one who owns the trap that you’ve taken.

398
00:43:13,500 --> 00:43:17,000
“You will only catch one.

399
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:22,000
“You will transfer what was to be yours to that person.”

400
00:43:23,700 --> 00:43:26,000
That’s another piece of traditional wisdom.

401
00:43:26,500 --> 00:43:29,500
And then some would also say

402
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:35,700
The legs of some who steal too much get crippled

403
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,500
Or their arms get crippled.

404
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:49,400
They say that shamans used to do that with their tools
to the people who did that a long time ago.

405
00:43:49,500 --> 00:43:56,800
They crippled their legs, and crippled their arms to make them suffer.

406
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:03,000
Those shamans made them like that with their tools
because they were unhappy with them.

407
00:44:03,100 --> 00:44:10,000
That’s why they especially warned us against taking a person’s things.

408
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:14,000
Behold the people these days.

409
00:44:14,500 --> 00:44:21,000
Because we do not teach that starting from when they’re growing

410
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:28,000
They run off with boats, and they steal a person’s boat motor

411
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:34,000
And they would steal a person’s entire drift net from his boat.

412
00:44:34,900 --> 00:44:45,000
They’ve probably become like that because they don’t hear about
the consequences of stealing and how dangerous it is

413
00:44:45,500 --> 00:44:51,000
Because we don’t admonish them against doing that.

414
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:55,500
And yet our ancestors strongly warned against it.

415
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:59,000
But they also had this traditional wisdom:

416
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:05,000
Let us try to make every one of our fellow people happy in our lives.

417
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:15,000
They said to look at these people who have always had things,
and they gather what they need.

418
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:19,000
They say that they’re like that through people’s gratitude.

419
00:45:19,500 --> 00:45:22,000
They say that gratitude is good.

420
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:27,000
And then I read this in the Bible:

421
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:38,000
Giving is more of a cause for gratitude than receiving.

422
00:45:38,500 --> 00:45:43,000
It’s a cause for gratitude to receive a gift

423
00:45:43,500 --> 00:45:48,500
But the Bible says that giving is more important

424
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:56,000
Because it says this: “Giving is more of a
cause for gratitude than receiving.”

425
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:08,500
That’s why our ancestors told us to help our fellow people
as a form of love if we have anything to spare.

426
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:14,000
They say that out a person’s gratitude

427
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:19,400
It’s like a person’s body is given strength.

428
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:22,300
God probably does that.

429
00:46:22,500 --> 00:46:29,000
They also told us to serve others in our lives.

430
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:35,500
And they say this: we will not deteriorate from our soles.

431
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:39,000
They say that.

432
00:46:39,100 --> 00:46:47,000
They say that as we serve, we will become stronger,
and sicknesses will not touch us.

433
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:54,000
Even if others are sick during an epidemic, they will not touch us.

434
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:59,000
That’s is the promise of servitude.

435
00:46:59,100 --> 00:47:03,000
A person will stand [alive] for a long time with any afflictions.

436
00:47:04,500 --> 00:47:09,000
This also concerns servitude: people are thankful.

437
00:47:09,300 --> 00:47:17,000
Or, if [s]he gets water or chops wood, an old woman or old man
can be thankful for that.

438
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:20,400
They say that his gratitude will uplift that person.

439
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:25,000
Those are our ancestors’ traditional wisdom.

440
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:31,000
I’ve said a lot by now.

441
00:47:31,100 --> 00:47:36,000
